overview: Jason began his career developing SoftWindows at Insignia in the UK. Following a jump across the pond, Jason joined Software Ventures and developed asynchronous implementations of all major Internet protocols, including SSL, for the small, fast Saturn web browser. At Bear River, he moved to server software, and pioneered the revolutionary Janx HTML transformation engine. Jason also serves as CTO of Armored Online, a provider of secure solutions for industries handling sensitive information. Jasonâ€™s interests extend to music and audio technology - from 2002 to 2006, he played keyboards for Oakland-based synthpop band The Lovemakers.
